			>
			<br><blockquote><hr>Kytherea wrote:<br><DIV>Now I do understand that the majority here felt SoD was already a rather weak ability for the cost and that now it is even moreso.</DIV><DIV>Ky</DIV><br><hr></blockquote><br><br>From what i saw, most necros thought of it as "balanced" (some thought of it as "weak", but usually can't say why because they didn't test it)<br>High cost (but consistent with the other GoD AAs)<br>Fairly long recast<br>Instant casting time (which is/was a great thing, no more wasting 10s to get back to regular killing style)<br>Fairly good burst damage<br>And a very important thing: SoD would fit your "playstyle" or "encounter": you could either play it "safe", stay far from encounter and get a ranged 50ish dps (without taking the risk to eat AEs or anything) or you could play it "tough", go in melee range (or turn around pets to keep mobs in melee range) with the risk of taking agro yourself or getting the pets to eat an AE/a riposte (remember: because of their low hps, they get 1rounded very easily by tier 2+ mobs) and waste most of their damages, but with the reward of potentially getting a doubled dps<br><br>I myself loved SoD, and i know quite a lot of other necros loved it too because it was fun, varied (aka you had many ways to use it) and far from overpowering
