			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Necromancers&message.id=1352#M1352">65</a> of 121
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 932 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>I posted this earlier on necro.eqclasses but figured it wouldnt hurt to put it here(cleaned up some of the language a bit as well):</P>
<P><SPAN class=postbody>Ok so i did some Swarm of decay tests last night, all from range just to see what sorta dmg these guys could reliably put out from range, against exp mobs in GoD, the expansion they should be tuned for imo. Well in Yxtta and Kod taz I tested them a total of 5 times. And just added up the damage. I was duoing with a bard so all mobs where rooted or within range of them the entire time and the mob lasted the full 1 minute duration so pets poofed before the target died. <BR><BR>Out of all 5 attempts the MAX dmg they did was 1851.... <BR>The minimum dmg was 1100ish. In all the parses the probabability of the arrows hitting for 16 (the minimum) was well over 50%. This is frankly just sad. These pets ARE way to low level and/or have way to&nbsp;low an atk amount to be considered anything but a heh look 3 skellies with bows COOL...... <BR>WTD is more burst dmg, lifeburn is more burst dmg, and this thing(Swarm of Decay)&nbsp;costs 30AA's.&nbsp; umm why??? <BR><BR>This AA needs to be changed to a 1 minute refresh like it was for a while in beta, or SERIOUSLY upped. I never liked the melee part of it being the reason it was good, but I think they gimped their range dmg as well, because I sure cant get them to parse even over 2k dmg anymore against exp mobs in the expansion they are from... Mobs tested against were all lvl 64-66 or so, and not kyvs who according to tongue quest mitigate arrows. <BR><BR>Quick Summary: <BR>Swarm of Decay does 1500 dmg every 30 minutes for 30AA's on average. (for argument sake we'll say 1800)<BR>Chance of each hit, hitting for minimum(16) well over 50% prolly 66%-75% <BR><BR>Conclusions: (we'll assume 1800 dmg as this is a high estimate and makes for nice numbers) <BR>SoD adds about 1DPS to a necro in an exp situation for 30 AA's. 1800dmg/1800 seconds between re-use = 1DPS. <BR><BR>SoD for the minute that it is up does 1800dmg/60seconds = 30 DPS. COME ON thats less than our pet does or even WTD pet, or even a&nbsp;bad dmg shield. 30 DPS from a burst situation AA is an absolute joke. If this ability is gonna stay how it is the reuse should be like 1-3 minutes. 30 AA's for a 10 DPS increase seems more reasonable, but I personally would rather have the burst DPS back and keep the re-use at 30. So that we would be a decent class to have in ikkinz 1 group trials as a DPS spot.&nbsp; This would be very easy to do just by giving these pets a significant Atk increase as their atk is simply to low for their arrows to hit hard with any regularity.</SPAN></P>
<DIV></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
