<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Necromancers&message.id=1434#M1434">73</a> of 121
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 684 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>I can not make a developer come post here but I did send him email with the following feedback and questions.&nbsp; Hopefully he will respond with some answers for these things and I will post what I get on it.</P>
<P><FONT size=2>*****</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>Is there any chance the Dev Team will consider lowering the AA cost and/or the recast timer on this new verison of Swarm of Decay? In it's current form, it is just not worth the AA cost and dealing with the long recast timer. Espically when I can use Wake the Dead every couple minutes, for less then 50% the AA cost.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>*****</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>Wizard AA - Call of Xuzl = 6 AA points, Refresh 15 min, Duration 45sec, approx 40dps burst (1800 dmg)</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>Mage AA - Host of the Elements = 12 AA points, Refresh 22 min, Duration 30sec, approx 180dps burst (5400 dmg)</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>Necro AA - Swarm of Decay = 30 AA points, Refresh 30 min, Duration 60 sec, approx 27dps burst (1600 dmg)</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2></FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>Looks to me like we need to get approximately 6x the damage out of this AA to make it comparable</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>to mage pets for damage / AA cost.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>******</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>Swarm of Decay does 1500 dmg every 30 minutes for 30AA's on average. (for argument sake we'll say 1800)</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>Chance of each hit, hitting for minimum(16) well over 50% prolly 66%-75% </FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>Conclusions: (we'll assume 1800 dmg as this is a high estimate and makes for nice numbers) </FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>SoD adds about 1DPS to a necro in an exp situation for 30 AA's. 1800dmg/1800 seconds between re-use = 1DPS. </FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>SoD for the minute that it is up does 1800dmg/60seconds = 30 DPS. COME ON thats less than our pet does or even WTD pet, or even a bad dmg shield. 30 DPS from a burst situation AA is an absolute joke. If this ability is gonna stay how it is the reuse should be like 1-3 minutes. 30 AA's for a 10 DPS increase seems more reasonable, but I personally would rather have the burst DPS back and keep the re-use at 30. So that we would be a decent class to have in ikkinz 1 group trials as a DPS spot. This would be very easy to do just by giving these pets a significant Atk increase as their atk is simply to low for their arrows to hit hard with any regularity.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>*****</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>The original SoD was underpowered, the nerfed version is useless.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>Given that the SoD AA was considered balanced during the beta process (I remember reading about the mele dps on the public Necro boards after the NDA was lifted but before GoD went live), and that subsequently a developer felt that the mele dps was too much, one of the following should be done:</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>1. Return SoD to its original version since it was considered balanced during beta (I realize this won't happen since a dev's ego is now at stake).</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>2. Leave the SoD mele damage as it currently is but raise the range (bow) damage to compensate.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>3. Leave the SoD mele and range damage as it is but lower the recast time to bring it in line with the DPS of other AAs of similar cost.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>4. Lower the cost of SoD to 12 AAs to bring it in line with other low DPS AAs.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>*****</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>I know you are unsatisfied with the answers I have given thus far and I will continue to try to get more information for you.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>Ky</FONT></P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<DIV></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Kytherea ~~wielding a giant hammer & a hairless War Hamster~~<br><br>"I'm late, I'm late...."
							</div>
								
